<c74object name="o.var" module="odot">

	<digest>
		Store a bundle and bang it out later
	</digest>

	<description>
		o.var copies an OSC packet and stores it for later use. Since FullPacket messages are references to data stored in memory, objects wishing to store a packet must make a copy of it rather than just save the FullPacket message. Use o.var or o.compose to store a packet, not zl ref or any other normal Max object.
	</description>

